msgid "\"[How to Become an Architect in 5 Steps](http://learn.org/articles/Architect_5_Steps_to_Becoming_an_Architect.html).\" Learn.org. Accessed January 14, 2017. "
msgstr ""

# Article is at <a href="http://translate.khanacademy.org/college-careers-more/career-content/career-profiles-build-and-fix-things/career-profile-architectural-designer/a/how-to-become-an-architect">http://translate.khanacademy.org/college-careers-more/career-content/career-profiles-build-and-fix-things/career-profile-architectural-designer/a/how-to-become-an-architect</a>.
# (KA_SOURCE_TREE: shared)
# (format: perseus_text)
#: intl/datastore:1
msgid "\"[How to Become an Architect](https://www.bls.gov/ooh/architecture-and-engineering/architects.htm#tab-4).\" U.S. Bureau of Labor Statistics. Accessed January 14, 2017."
msgstr ""

# Article is at <a href="http://translate.khanacademy.org/college-careers-more/career-content/career-profiles-build-and-fix-things/career-profile-architectural-designer/a/how-to-become-an-architect">http://translate.khanacademy.org/college-careers-more/career-content/career-profiles-build-and-fix-things/career-profile-architectural-designer/a/how-to-become-an-architect</a>.
# (KA_SOURCE_TREE: shared)
# (format: perseus_text)
#: intl/datastore:1
msgid "Deciding to become an architect is a big commitment. Architects are responsible for the safety and happiness of the people who live or work in the spaces they design. Because of this, the process of becoming an architect is a long and challenging one—it can take up to 10 years! "
msgstr ""

# Article is at <a href="http://translate.khanacademy.org/college-careers-more/career-content/career-profiles-build-and-fix-things/career-profile-architectural-designer/a/how-to-become-an-architect">http://translate.khanacademy.org/college-careers-more/career-content/career-profiles-build-and-fix-things/career-profile-architectural-designer/a/how-to-become-an-architect</a>.
# (KA_SOURCE_TREE: shared)
# (format: perseus_text)
#: intl/datastore:1
msgid "From this point, the path toward becoming a professional architect splits. Each state has its own certification requirements—although there are some common elements. Every state requires architects to pass the Architect Registration Examination, or ARE. Some states require architects to pass additional state exams before granting certification. "
msgstr ""

# Article is at <a href="http://translate.khanacademy.org/college-careers-more/career-content/career-profiles-build-and-fix-things/career-profile-architectural-designer/a/how-to-become-an-architect">http://translate.khanacademy.org/college-careers-more/career-content/career-profiles-build-and-fix-things/career-profile-architectural-designer/a/how-to-become-an-architect</a>.
# (KA_SOURCE_TREE: shared)
# (format: perseus_text)
#: intl/datastore:1
msgid "If the college you attend requires an internship as part of your graduation requirements, you’ll already have some experience under your belt. But, because most states require around three years of experience hours before they will grant an architect certification, new graduates with a bachelor or master of architecture need to find a position as an architectural designer with an architecture firm. "
msgstr ""

# Article is at <a href="http://translate.khanacademy.org/college-careers-more/career-content/career-profiles-build-and-fix-things/career-profile-architectural-designer/a/how-to-become-an-architect">http://translate.khanacademy.org/college-careers-more/career-content/career-profiles-build-and-fix-things/career-profile-architectural-designer/a/how-to-become-an-architect</a>.
# (KA_SOURCE_TREE: shared)
# (format: perseus_text)
#: intl/datastore:1
msgid "If you already know that you might want to study architecture in college, you should start preparing the foundational skills you’ll need in college while you’re still in high school. Make sure you’re taking classes that develop your math and computer skills. Are there any after-school clubs that would allow you to learn computer aided drafting, or CAD?"
msgstr ""

# Article is at <a href="http://translate.khanacademy.org/college-careers-more/career-content/career-profiles-build-and-fix-things/career-profile-architectural-designer/a/how-to-become-an-architect">http://translate.khanacademy.org/college-careers-more/career-content/career-profiles-build-and-fix-things/career-profile-architectural-designer/a/how-to-become-an-architect</a>.
# (KA_SOURCE_TREE: shared)
# (format: perseus_text)
#: intl/datastore:1
msgid "Once an architect has received state licensure, they may use one of several professional suffixes. AIA indicates that an architect is an American Institute for Architects member and is licensed or registered. RA means that the architect is registered. NCARB means that the architect is a National Council of Architectural Registration Board member and that they have passed the ARE exams."
msgstr ""

# Article is at <a href="http://translate.khanacademy.org/college-careers-more/career-content/career-profiles-build-and-fix-things/career-profile-architectural-designer/a/how-to-become-an-architect">http://translate.khanacademy.org/college-careers-more/career-content/career-profiles-build-and-fix-things/career-profile-architectural-designer/a/how-to-become-an-architect</a>.
# (KA_SOURCE_TREE: shared)
# (format: perseus_text)
#: intl/datastore:1
msgid "Once you graduate from high school, you’ll need to attend a university with an architecture program accredited by the National Architectural Accrediting Board. Most undergraduate programs in architecture demand a five-year course of study that may include time spent working as a paid intern at an architecture firm. Some architects continue on to receive a master’s of architecture degree, or M.Arch. The majority of state certification processes require candidates to hold a degree in architecture."
msgstr ""

