#: intl/datastore:1
msgid "How do you become a hair stylist?"
msgstr ""

# Description of tutorial article <a href="http://translate.khanacademy.org/college-careers-more/career-content/career-profiles-start-a-business/career-profile-hairstylist/a/how-do-you-become-a-hair-stylist">http://translate.khanacademy.org/college-careers-more/career-content/career-profiles-start-a-business/career-profile-hairstylist/a/how-do-you-become-a-hair-stylist</a>
# (KA_SOURCE_TREE: shared)
# (format: html)
#: intl/datastore:1
msgid "Before you pick up the scissors and start styling hair, you&#39;ll need training and a license!"
msgstr ""

# Article is at <a href="http://translate.khanacademy.org/college-careers-more/career-content/career-profiles-start-a-business/career-profile-hairstylist/a/how-do-you-become-a-hair-stylist">http://translate.khanacademy.org/college-careers-more/career-content/career-profiles-start-a-business/career-profile-hairstylist/a/how-do-you-become-a-hair-stylist</a>.
# (KA_SOURCE_TREE: shared)
# (format: perseus_text)
#: intl/datastore:1
msgid "Hair stylists are responsible for not only the look of a client’s hair, but also the health of the hair and their client’s safety. Before giving a perm or a dramatic asymmetrical cut, you’re going to need an education and a license. "
msgstr ""

# Article is at <a href="http://translate.khanacademy.org/college-careers-more/career-content/career-profiles-start-a-business/career-profile-hairstylist/a/how-do-you-become-a-hair-stylist">http://translate.khanacademy.org/college-careers-more/career-content/career-profiles-start-a-business/career-profile-hairstylist/a/how-do-you-become-a-hair-stylist</a>.
# (KA_SOURCE_TREE: shared)
# (format: perseus_text)
#: intl/datastore:1
msgid "Hairstylists typically undergo additional training to master new techniques and learn about the latest products. Some states require stylists to take continuing education classes focused on style and/or public health in order to maintain their license. Even when continuing education isn’t required, reading hair magazines and participating in workshops can help you stay current and avoid giving someone a haircut that was better left in the 80s. "
msgstr ""

# Article is at <a href="http://translate.khanacademy.org/college-careers-more/career-content/career-profiles-start-a-business/career-profile-hairstylist/a/how-do-you-become-a-hair-stylist">http://translate.khanacademy.org/college-careers-more/career-content/career-profiles-start-a-business/career-profile-hairstylist/a/how-do-you-become-a-hair-stylist</a>.
# (KA_SOURCE_TREE: shared)
# (format: perseus_text)
#: intl/datastore:1
msgid "If you want to someday manage a salon or even open a salon of your own, taking business classes at a local community college can also help you develop important management skills to complement your styling prowess. "
msgstr ""

# Article is at <a href="http://translate.khanacademy.org/college-careers-more/career-content/career-profiles-start-a-business/career-profile-hairstylist/a/how-do-you-become-a-hair-stylist">http://translate.khanacademy.org/college-careers-more/career-content/career-profiles-start-a-business/career-profile-hairstylist/a/how-do-you-become-a-hair-stylist</a>.
# (KA_SOURCE_TREE: shared)
# (format: perseus_text)
#: intl/datastore:1
msgid "The qualifications for licensure vary from state to state. In order to gain a licence as a hair stylist, most states require you to be at least 16, have a high school diploma or GED, and complete a state-licensed cosmetology program. It is important to check the licensing requirements in your state before selecting a school to complete your training.  After completing the program, prospective stylists may be required to do both a written exam and a practical exam."
msgstr ""

# Article is at <a href="http://translate.khanacademy.org/college-careers-more/career-content/career-profiles-start-a-business/career-profile-hairstylist/a/how-do-you-become-a-hair-stylist">http://translate.khanacademy.org/college-careers-more/career-content/career-profiles-start-a-business/career-profile-hairstylist/a/how-do-you-become-a-hair-stylist</a>.
# (KA_SOURCE_TREE: shared)
# (format: perseus_text)
#: intl/datastore:1
msgid "When selecting a cosmetology program, do your research to make sure the program is accredited and fits with your long-term goals. Cosmetology programs require a commitment of both time and money. Full-time programs typically last 9 months. In a rural area, a cosmetology program will cost at least \\$6,000 and that number rises to at least \\$10,000 in urban areas. Some private programs can cost twice that amount. One benefit of completing a full cosmetology program is that they often provide students with training in makeup, skin care, and nails, in addition to hair. "
msgstr ""

# Article is at <a href="http://translate.khanacademy.org/college-careers-more/career-content/career-profiles-start-a-business/career-profile-hairstylist/a/how-do-you-become-a-hair-stylist">http://translate.khanacademy.org/college-careers-more/career-content/career-profiles-start-a-business/career-profile-hairstylist/a/how-do-you-become-a-hair-stylist</a>.
