# (KA_SOURCE_TREE: shared)
# (format: perseus_text)
#: intl/datastore:1
msgid "According to the US Bureau of Labor Statistics, the median pay for a commercial airline pilot in 2015 was \\$102,520 per year. Other benefits may include 401K, medical, dental, life insurance, and flight benefits for the pilot and their family members. While commercial airline pilots rarely have standard weekends, they may have 9-14 days off each month. "
msgstr ""

# Article is at <a href="http://translate.khanacademy.org/college-careers-more/career-content/travel-and-explore/career-profile-commercial-airline-pilot/a/what-does-a-commercial-airline-pilot-do">http://translate.khanacademy.org/college-careers-more/career-content/travel-and-explore/career-profile-commercial-airline-pilot/a/what-does-a-commercial-airline-pilot-do</a>.
# (KA_SOURCE_TREE: shared)
# (format: perseus_text)
#: intl/datastore:1
msgid "If you picture a commercial airline pilot, the image that comes to mind is likely of someone sitting in the cockpit of a large plane, flying people to destinations around the word. Yet not all commercial pilots work for large passenger airlines. They also fly small groups on tours and do quick commuter flights within their local region. "
msgstr ""

# Article is at <a href="http://translate.khanacademy.org/college-careers-more/career-content/travel-and-explore/career-profile-commercial-airline-pilot/a/what-does-a-commercial-airline-pilot-do">http://translate.khanacademy.org/college-careers-more/career-content/travel-and-explore/career-profile-commercial-airline-pilot/a/what-does-a-commercial-airline-pilot-do</a>.
