# (KA_SOURCE_TREE: shared)
# (format: perseus_text)
#: intl/datastore:1
msgid "To ensure a safe flight, the pilot starts each trip by checking the maintenance log book of the aircraft, weather information, the flight plan, and the fuel plan. They also communicate with team members such as the ground crew and dispatcher; if flying for a passenger airline, they also communicate with the flight crew and passengers. Each flight may require them to work with a new team of people and adjust to different work styles and personalities. "
msgstr ""

# Article is at <a href="http://translate.khanacademy.org/college-careers-more/career-content/travel-and-explore/career-profile-commercial-airline-pilot/a/what-does-a-commercial-airline-pilot-do">http://translate.khanacademy.org/college-careers-more/career-content/travel-and-explore/career-profile-commercial-airline-pilot/a/what-does-a-commercial-airline-pilot-do</a>.
# (KA_SOURCE_TREE: shared)
# (format: perseus_text)
#: intl/datastore:1
msgid "When entering this field, a new pilot typically starts as a first officer flying small planes before moving up to captain. Once they gain experience they can move up to larger airlines, flying larger body planes to further destinations. As pilots gain seniority, they also have more control over their schedule and destinations. "
msgstr ""

